Roh asked the National Intelligence Service (NIS), the country's main spy agency, to launch a "thorough" investigation into the case, his spokesman Kim Man-Soo said.
Hong, the publisher of leading newspaper Joongang Ilbo, was named as the country's top envoy in Washington in February.
South Korean television and newspapers have released what they called a taped private conversation between ambassador Hong Seok-Hyun and a top official of the country's largest conglomerate Samsung in 1997.
The influential civic group also called for criminal charges against former government officials suspected of having received bribes from Samsung.
